You need to create a Bash script that will loop continually and perform some commandswithin the loop. Which of the following lines will accomplish this task?
A)  if [ $exit - eq "exit" ]
B)  while true; do
C)  for ($i = 0, $i++)
D)  continue until ($exit)
B
B. A while loop that evaluates boolean true will accomplish the task described. The otheroptions given are syntactically incorrect in various ways.
